    "body": "@funkyfuture if you want a docker image without the notebook, it probably doesn't make sense to use IPython as a base image, since installing IPython is just `pip install ipython`, and there are no services to run. Starting with 4.0, the `ipython/ipython`image is deprecated, and we don't plan to maintain a base docker image for IPython anymore. If you want the notebook, you can use `jupyter/notebook` or one of the docker-stacks images.\n"
