    "body": "It does seem reasonable that people would want an ipython console docker image, I end up using notebook images for that all the time. As for us maintaining it, we wouldn't want it pinned to the latest whims on master. Seems more like something to contribute to the docker-library image suite (`ipython:3`, `ipython:2`, `notebook`, ... etc.)\n"
